\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\lang9 I want to make a webapplication where I can control an LED display made up of circular nodes 42mm and 60mm in diameter, so  small and large nodes respectively. \par
The small node is comprised of 3 rings of LEDs (sk9812) the inner ring has 5 LEDS, the middle ring has 10 LEDs, the outer most ring has 15 LEDs.These rings will be treated as one colour each , so 3 colour values (RGB) will be sent for each ring in a node. \par
The large node is also comprised of 3 rings of LEDs(sk9812) , the inner ring has 8 LEDs, the middle ring has 14 LEDs, the outer ring has 22 LEDs. These rings will be treated as one colour each , so 3 colour values (RGB) will be sent for each ring in a node. \par
There are a total of 9 LED strands of varying lengths of nodes. Each of the 9 strands data pins connects to a GPIO pin on the Teensy 4.1. Pins 0-8 are allocated for each of the LED strand's Data pins. Pin 9 on the teensy 4.1 is allocated for the CLK pin for all the strands CLK. \par
The teensy 4.1 is connected via an ethernet port to a computer, it also has a sufficient power supply. I do not want to exceed a brightness level above 30/255 for any LED ring so this should be a variable in the code\par
There are 2 strands with large nodes and the rest are small node strands. \par
The json file called  pin_nodes.json contains the strand's GPIO pin on the teensy , whether it is a small or large node type, the position data for that node in a strand, (i have specified 3 types of position please choose which one you think will work best for the visualisation for future animated content tests) , the index of the node, and finally i require 3 rings on each node that represent the physical led rings for each node type as mentioned above. \par
I would liked to create a webUI for this LED display that looks like a squid once all the nodes are arranged in their positions, I would like the nodes to mimic chromataphore cell behaviour like on real squid and cuttlefish the cells pulsate , expand and contract , so the rings would fade up and down from inner to outer to represent that behaviour. \par
I would like there to be a control for a noise shader or a set of 3 noise shaders that can alter the brightness of each ring on each node but across the LED canvas. I would also like there to be the ability of controlling the colour of each ring across the canvas using the noise shader . So i would like to control the scale of the shader , how much black and or colour type is in it. \par
It would be good to also be able to add a layer for an effector say a sphere travelling over the canvas  to represent some kind of interference so in the future i may have an Arducam plugged in to see if a person walks by and the LED nodes mimic the colours the person is wearing and tracks their position by expanding or contracting the chromataphore cells so the led rings on the nodes. \par
